Interface Render.Cell.Interpreter<C extends javax.swing.JComponent,V>

  • Type Parameters:
    C - The type of the component which is used to render the cell.
    V - The type of the value of the cell.
    Enclosing interface:
    Render.Cell<C extends javax.swing.JComponent,V>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface Render.Cell.Interpreter<C extends javax.swing.JComponent,V>
    An interface for interpreting the value of a Render.Cell and setting a Component or custom renderer which is then used to render the cell. Use Render.Cell.setRenderer(Component) or Render.Cell.setRenderer(Consumer) to define how the cell should be rendered exactly.
